Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '464̣' Name Damokrates. Five examples in the Benaki collection, Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, are from the same die, including ABC 0339.39.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (127)
